ARM GAS  /tmp/ccb11GdC.s 			page 51


 890:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY calls an ISR safe FreeRTOS API
 891:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			function.  ISR safe FreeRTOS API functions must *only* be called
 892:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			from interrupts that have been assigned a priority at or below
 893:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY.
 894:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 
 895:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			Numerically low interrupt priority numbers represent logically high
 896:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			interrupt priorities, therefore the priority of the interrupt must
 897:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			be set to a value equal to or numerically *higher* than
 898:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY.
 899:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 
 900:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			Interrupts that	use the FreeRTOS API must not be left at their
 901:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			default priority of	zero as that is the highest possible priority,
 902:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			which is guaranteed to be above configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY,
 903:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			and	therefore also guaranteed to be invalid.
 904:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 
 905:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			FreeRTOS maintains separate thread and ISR API functions to ensure
 906:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			interrupt entry is as fast and simple as possible.
 907:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 
 908:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			The following links provide detailed information:
 909:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			http://www.freertos.org/RTOS-Cortex-M3-M4.html
 910:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			http://www.freertos.org/FAQHelp.html */
 911:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 			configASSERT( ucCurrentPriority >= ucMaxSysCallPriority );
