 914:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		/* Priority grouping:  The interrupt controller (NVIC) allows the bits
 915:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		that define each interrupt's priority to be split between bits that
 916:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		define the interrupt's pre-emption priority bits and bits that define
 917:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		the interrupt's sub-priority.  For simplicity all bits must be defined
 918:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		to be pre-emption priority bits.  The following assertion will fail if
 919:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		this is not the case (if some bits represent a sub-priority).
 920:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 
 921:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		If the application only uses CMSIS libraries for interrupt
 922:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4_MPU/port.c **** 		configuration then the correct setting can be achieved on all Cortex-M
